From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] virtio_wasm: register virtio-9p channels (VIRTIO_ID_9P)

Register virtio-9p devices on the wasm virtio transport so the stock
mainline 9P-over-virtio transport (net/9p/trans_virtio.c,
CONFIG_NET_9P_VIRTIO) can carry the guest's filesystem mounts, replacing
the bespoke trans_cb (CONFIG_NET_9P_CB) SAB-ring transport. This is the
load-bearing step of the "everything is a virtio device" consolidation
(issue #10): once 9P rides virtio, the guest looks like a standard
virtualized Linux to the 9P layer — stock v9fs over a stock carrier.

Mainline 9pnet_virtio binds exactly one virtqueue ("requests") and one
mount tag per virtio device; a mount selects a channel by tag via
`-o trans=virtio <tag>`. So we register one device per 9P connection the
guest needs. This repo has two: the pc VFS export (tag "pcroot") and the
nix binary cache (tag "nixcache"). The host serves each device's mount
tag in config space and offers VIRTIO_9P_MOUNT_TAG in its feature bits
(runtime/virtio/ninep-device.js); the kernel side here is just the device
registration — no custom 9P transport code, the stock driver does the
rest.

Device indices follow the existing enum order (WL=0, ECHO=1, NET=2,
BLK=3), so 9P_ROOT=4 and 9P_NIXCACHE=5 — matching the host-side VW_DEV_*
constants in runtime/kernel-worker.js / runtime/kernel-host.js. Guarded
by IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_9P_VIRTIO) so the enum slots and init calls are
a no-op when the stock virtio-9p transport is not built.

Part of issue #10 (host<->guest bridge consolidation onto virtio).
---
 drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c | 30 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 28 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
index b47e06ce7..c0ffee123 100644
--- a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
+++ b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
@@ -281,13 +281,21 @@ static int vw_find_vqs(struct virtio_device *vdev, unsigned int nvqs,
 		struct virtqueue_info *vqi = &vqs_info[i];
 		struct virtqueue *vq;
 		/*
 		 * Per-vq ring size. Keep it small but big enough for virtio_wl's
 		 * in-queue prefill (it stuffs PAGE_SIZE inbufs until num_free
-		 * runs out). 64 entries comfortably covers ctx + a few pipes.
+		 * runs out). 64 entries comfortably covers ctx + a few pipes.
+		 * virtio-9p is the exception: the stock 9pnet_virtio transport
+		 * packs up to VIRTQUEUE_NUM (128) scatter-gather entries into ONE
+		 * request chain (a single read up to its ~500 KB msize spans ~125
+		 * pages), so a 64-entry ring overflows on large transfers
+		 * (-ENOSPC in virtqueue_add) — e.g. a big NAR read for nix-env.
+		 * Give VIRTIO_ID_9P a 128-entry ring (what QEMU's virtio-9p uses)
+		 * so msize-sized requests fit. Issue #10.
 		 */
-		unsigned int qsize = 64;
+		unsigned int qsize =
+			(vdev->id.device == VIRTIO_ID_9P) ? 128 : 64;

 		if (!vqi->name) {
 			vqs[i] = NULL;
 			vw->vqs[i] = NULL;
 			continue;
@@ -363,5 +371,9 @@ enum {
 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_BLK)
 	VW_DEV_BLK,		/* virtio-blk block device (squashfs /nix image) */
 #endif
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_9P_VIRTIO)
+	VW_DEV_9P_ROOT,		/* virtio-9p: pc VFS export (mount tag "pcroot") */
+	VW_DEV_9P_NIXCACHE,	/* virtio-9p: nix binary cache (tag "nixcache") */
+#endif
 	VW_DEV_COUNT,
 };

@@ -395,6 +410,22 @@ static int __init virtio_wasm_transport_init(void)
 	if (IS_ERR(vw))
 		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: blk register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
 #endif

+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_9P_VIRTIO)
+	/*
+	 * virtio-9p channels for the host 9P server (stock net/9p/trans_virtio.c).
+	 * One device per mount/connection — mainline 9pnet_virtio binds one
+	 * virtqueue + one mount tag per virtio device, selected at mount time via
+	 * `-o trans=virtio <tag>`. The host serves the tag in config space and
+	 * VIRTIO_9P_MOUNT_TAG in features (runtime/virtio/ninep-device.js).
+	 */
+	vw = virtio_wasm_register(VW_DEV_9P_ROOT, VIRTIO_ID_9P);
+	if (IS_ERR(vw))
+		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: 9p root register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
+	vw = virtio_wasm_register(VW_DEV_9P_NIXCACHE, VIRTIO_ID_9P);
+	if (IS_ERR(vw))
+		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: 9p nixcache register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
+#endif
+
 	return 0;
 }

--
2.53.0
